node.text:
Sharing my recipe on IGTV since most of you haven’t seen the full YouTube video & it’s important for me to keep spreading the food I grew up on!

The irony is that while editing this, I was reckoning with the fact that I’m generally not considered “Filipino” by those in the Philippines even though I’m so proud of my heritage 😕

I was just called an entitled “pseudo-Filipino” in the comments of the last post by @barkadadc, a white-owned wine bar that got backlash for naming itself Barkada, a meaningful Tagalog word for deep friendship. They were serving wine & charcuterie instead of any Filipino items with no intention of promoting Filipino culture beyond their name. In their words to @eater_dc, they “didn’t want to call it posse or homies or clique” so they went with Barkada because “it helped that bar is in the word” 🤨

Countless Filipino-Americans (Fil-Ams) pressured them to agree to change their name (though that name change has yet to happen 🧐). I personally saw it as stealing a great name from a potential business that would actually promote Filipino culture, like @barkadahollywood has done in LA. But Filipinos largely condoned keeping the name, calling Fil-Ams overly sensitive and touting that they’re “proud” to see non-Filipinos “spreading our culture” even though this business was NOT actually doing so with their $17 glasses of Spanish wine and cheese plates. They were appropriating, not appreciating. 

I got into debates (and welcome more below) because I couldn’t understand why Filipinos were so adamantly defending white men appropriating our language when they could instead support the name change, which would open the door for a Barkada DC that HONORS our culture. So consider this a call to my fellow Fil-Ams in the DC area to capitalize on this media hype and open the Barkada DC the community deserves 🙏🏽

Filipino food is not that widespread. We still have a chance to open authentic places to educate people before our cuisine gets bastardized the way others have. I know I’m going to keep doing my part to share the food I grew up on, and I hope you all try out a recipe yourself to learn to love it too ❤️
https://bit.ly/FilipinoChickenAdobo

Tag me so I can see how you do! I’ll repost my favorites on my story #IndulgentEatsHK

node.text:
I was lucky to find @thecollectivekitchen to cook for us in the comfort of our own chalet since booking restaurants proved to be difficult for our large group for our snowboarding trip. They set the bar sooo high with their incredible food & service for our 2 private dinners & breakfast, all at the same or even lower cost as dining out in Whistler but with the perk of drinking our own alcohol and not having to leave the house. Can’t recommend them enough if you’re planning a ski trip this season! Everything shown on the video was delicious, but I’ve marked our group's favorite dishes - which ones do you want to try most?
- Hanger Steak & Braised Beef Short Ribs
- Thai Lobster Salad with burrata ⭐️
- Kuri Squash Ravioli with brown butter and hazelnuts ⭐️
- Miso Marinated Black Cod with shiitake mushrooms
- Fresh Tagliatelle with parmesan & herbs
- Yukon Gold Mashed Potatoes ⭐️
- Toffee Cheesecake ⭐️
- Sticky Toffee Pudding ⭐️
- Chocolate Mousse
- Flat Iron Steak and Eggs ⭐️
- Huevos Rancheros
- Eggs Benedict with maple fennel bacon ⭐️
- Toasted Ricotta Gnocchi ⭐️
- Fresh Dungeness Crab Salad
- Berkshire 10oz Bone in Pork Chop with roast onion & apple ⭐️
- Stone Ground Polenta with parmesan ⭐️
- Slow Cooked Lamb Shank
- Apple Beignets
Beanie: @piccoliny #IndulgentEatsWhistler #IndulgentEatsCanada

Comin’ in hot with all the Sichuan food for our first dinner out of quarantine! 🌶🍜🔥 @sijie_sichuan is one of my faves in HK for a group dinner - you pay a fixed price per head and the more people in your group, the more dishes you get to try off the menu (plus it’s BYOB!) 🍷

The Sichuan style cold noodles here are a must-order, as are the salt and pepper fried shrimp that you are so crispy, you can eat the whole thing with the head on 🦐💯 I do wish the food was spicier, so if you do go def ask for it spicier if you can handle it! Tag your crew who you need to try this with #IndulgentEatsHK

LAST DAY of our hotel quarantine at @kerryhotelhk! 🥳 We’ve been waking up with the sunrise (thanks jet lag!) to work out since we rented a rowing machine and had a friend drop off my @whitelabelling yoga mat plus booty bands & a jump rope 🚣🏻‍♀️ It’s felt great to reset our bodies to prep for a return to @hybridgymhk after 3 weeks of max indulgence in NYC (see my Body Positivity highlight for more on this!) 💪🏽

Then our first delicious meal of the day arrives around 7AM - I’ll highlight our meals & full quarantine experience in a future video so comment with any questions you want me to address!

HK has some of the strictest quarantine rules in the world in its (frankly unrealistic) effort to keep zero cases of COVID. We got so lucky that we only had to pay for 1 week of quarantine - they relaxed the rules less than 2 months ago so vaxxed individuals could reduce quarantine from 14 days to 7 with an antibody test, making everyone jump to book trips to visit their home countries for the 1st time in 2 years 🛫

But then the gov’t had a quick about face — starting today all inbound travelers from “high-risk” countries (like the US) have to quarantine for 21 days in a hotel that you pay for, a change that was only announced 4 days ago. It’s left HK residents who went back home stranded, unable to return since airlines require provide proof of a 21 day quarantine hotel booking and all of the hotels have been fully booked for months.

It’s shame that the HK gov’t left so many of its citizens down instead of using this as an opportunity to get vax rates up (it’s a low 40% in HK) since the Pfizer-BioNTech vaccine has proven effective in preventing hospitalizations against the Delta variant in the US. The US was classified as high risk to begin with because many states are facing surges of cases and awful levels of hospitalizations, of which 95%+ are unvaccinated individuals who are clogging up the health care system. All of this to say that I implore everyone around the world to GET VAXXED so we can protect each other, get borders to reopen, and eventually get back to some level of normalcy. PLEASE and thank you 🙏🏽 #IndulgentEatsHK

SOUND ON for KBBQ sizzle plus cute commentary from my parents 🔥🥺 Mike and I took both of our parents to one of my fave spots @baekjongnyc after being tourists for the day at @edgenyc and it was the perfect meal for our big group 🇰🇷💯 The full video of our experience is on YouTube - link in bio!

We had a private room to enjoy ALL the delicious high quality cuts of beef and pork (marinated short rib and crispy pork belly FTW) 🥩🍖🙌🏽 It was our parents’ first time having KBBQ where they cook the meat for you and also trying dishes like cheese corn (which is unlimited here along with the egg) and they LOVED it 😋 Shoutout to David for cooking for us and even accommodating Mike’s mom who wanted burnt edges on her beef 👏🏽

And don’t forget the sides! The crispy mandu 🥟, tteokbokki (spicy rice cakes) and haemul pajeon (seafood pancake) are always must adds here. What’s your fave dish at KBBQ? #IndulgentEatsNYC

You NEED to try the Gotham Smash 🍔 by my man @gothamburgersocialclub! It takes the classic burger to a new level by smashing onions directly into @newyorkvalleywagyu patties topped with American cheese, sauce & pickles in squishy @potatorolls 🤤

Mike Puma and I go way back from when we both started on Instagram, and it’s been awesome to see him transform his passion for burgers into pop-ups that helped bars serve food when NYC’s COVID rules initially required them to do so. Now he’s continuing to smash his seriously great burgers at regular pop-ups, including one TONIGHT at @raysbarnyc from 5PM on so you know what your dinner plans are, NYC friends!

And be sure to follow @gothamburgersocialclub to see where his next pop-up will be so you can try this burger 😛 #IndulgentEatsNYC #GothamBurgerSocialClub

node.text:
NYC photo dump since it’s been such an absolute dream that I haven’t had any time to edit my videos yet 😅🗽❤️ But SAVE THIS POST for just a snapshot of fun places to visit and a few of my fave spots I got to revisit 🍕🥯

I’m writing this with tears in my eyes at the airport because I can’t believe our amazing 3 week trip is already over 😢 While it still felt like we missed out on a lot in this condensed time, it was unreal to spend time with family & friends after this tumultuous 2 years 🥰😭

We also explored SO many different neighborhoods and even hit all 5 boroughs today alone thanks to our stay in Brooklyn, a visit to @nybg in the Bronx, a drive through Staten Island to get to the airport, plus a bonus Jersey City trip to say farewell to family over @razzanj pizza 🍕 

We’ll be trapped in hotel quarantine in HK for a week starting tomorrow 😒 BUT I’ll have uninterrupted time to edit and share all the incredible eats we had, so stay tuned! #IndulgentEatsNYC

Making it rain truffles AND casino winnings is my new summer vibe thanks to @theoceanac 💸 Had such a delicious dinner at Dolce Mare to kick off our little family and friends reunion in Atlantic City, and it was the perfect spot for Italian family-style feasting.

You MUST get the seafood risotto that legit had equal ratios of rice to scallops/shrimp/squid/clams - so good 🦐🦑 Other standouts were the summer ravioli with fresh shaved truffle, octopus, bolognese, and lobster ravioli. 

Def check out #TheOceanAC for delicious dining and a nice escape from the city! And excuse my raspy voice in the video - I lost it screaming with excitement over winning at slots 😂🎰🤑#OceanACPartner #IndulgentEatsNJ #OceanACEats

🗽 BACK IN NYC for the next few weeks so I’m celebrating with the BRUNCHWRAP 2.0 🇵🇭🌯🙌🏽 Come party at @flipsigi with @fork_knife and I this Sunday August 1 from 12-3PM or try it all August long with a special discount for my followers, see below! 🤑

Our upgraded version of the smash hit #BrunchwrapSupreme has longganisa, a crispy sinigang hashbrown, cheesy egg, guac, lettuce, tomato, banana ketchup & home run sauce, wrapped up like my fave Crunchwrap from @tacobell and it’s BOMB 💣

Starting Sunday you order on @flipsigi’s website (linked on my story) and use my code INDULGENT to get 15% off the Brunchwrap 2.0 to enjoy at our Sunday Funday party with live music, or all month long.

Plus @hungryartistny created an illustration of the Brunchwrap so you can order your own print at the party this Sunday to get a piece of Flip Sigi on your walls 🖼 Can’t wait to meet you guys and for you to try the Brunchwrap! #IndulgentEatsNYC #IndulgentEatsFilipino
